Strategic Assessment

alpha strike melee focused

This army is a high-pressure 'Wolf Jail' list designed to overwhelm opponents through Turn 1 Deep Strike aggression and extreme durability. By leveraging Logan Grimnar's ability to bring heavy hitters in early, it forces the opponent to play defensively from the first activation while durable Terminators and Thunderwolf Cavalry grind down the mid-board.

SUPPORT

— Force multipliers
Bjorn the Fell-Handed (160pts)
SUPPORT

"Keep him near the center of your line to generate CP and act as a durable anchor with his half-damage ability. His primary role is survival; don't throw him into a suicidal charge early when his CP generation is most valuable. He is vulnerable to being kited by high-speed anti-tank units that outrange his flamer and cannon."

Logan Grimnar (110pts)
SUPPORT

"His most powerful tool is enabling a Turn 1 Deep Strike for his bodyguard unit; use this to pressure the opponent's home objective immediately. Save his 'Howling Onslaught' for Turn 3 to repeat the Ferocious Strike pack for a finishing blow. He is vulnerable if his unit is destroyed, as his individual combat output is good but not game-ending."

Wolf Guard Battle Leader (90pts)
SUPPORT

"Attach to the Wolf Guard Headtakers to grant them Sustained Hits and Lance via Skjald's Foretelling. This makes the unit a legitimate threat to heavy vehicles on the charge. Watch out for Precision fire, as his 5 wounds won't last long against dedicated snipers."
